hopobject.body: Where do you come from? montelukast sodium drugs.com He was right to be worried. According to government statistics, two people died last year from barbecue-related injuries and another 19 ended up in hospital. It may not sound like a lot, but when you factor in the poor weather last summer and thus the relatively low number of barbecues being lit, it’s more significant. And the figure doesn’t include the less serious, but still painful minor burns that involve a lot of holding your hand under the tap – hardly the stuff of a relaxed party atmosphere.
